ts=2026-05-21T02:10:11.257Z type=decision scope=module:_core content="In Alternative B, do not expose a public spread API; pre_series/post_series spread behavior should be inferred internally by _core."
ts=2026-05-21T02:10:11.257Z type=decision scope=project content="typstpy behavior changes must update the corresponding docstring doctests because doctests are planned to be collected into tests/fixtures/test.typ and compiled with Typst for validation."
ts=2026-05-21T02:46:13.790Z type=decision scope=module:_core content="Alternative B for typstpy keeps spread inference internal rather than exposing a public spread API; doctests should document changed behavior."
ts=2026-05-21T02:46:13.790Z type=decision scope=project content="typstpy now targets Python >=3.11, uses Pyright basic for type checking, and includes py.typed for typed package consumers."
ts=2026-05-21T02:46:13.790Z type=pattern scope=project content="Public parameter validation in typstpy should use explicit ValueError or TypeError, not assert."
ts=2026-05-21T04:33:27.469Z type=decision scope=project content="Development scripts live under scripts/; README generation defaults to stdout and clipboard use is explicit via --clipboard."
ts=2026-05-21T04:33:27.469Z type=decision scope=project content="The Typst fixture is generated from _Implement registry docstring examples with python scripts/generate_typst_fixture.py --write tests/fixtures/test.typ; Typst CLI tests skip when typst is unavailable."
ts=2026-05-21T14:37:10.011Z type=decision scope=project content="Project has an opencode skill `typst-doc-verify` at `.opencode/skills/typst-doc-verify/SKILL.md` for verifying one or more functions against official Typst docs and maintaining Better Notes comments: `# *` for verified, `# TODO` for mismatch or inconclusive."
